Cummins Engine Co said it willtemporarily recall about 150 production workers at itsColumbus-area plants because it sees a moderate upturn in NorthAmerican demand for heavy-duty truck engines.    The company said the recalls will begin March 30.    Production rates for Cummins' heavy-duty truck engines haveincreased about 10 pct over fourth-quarter levels and shouldstay at these levels through the first half of 1987, Cumminssaid.    The company also reported some upswing in demand for itscomponents and service parts. Reuter&#3;